<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
   <div class="col-lg-5"><div class="well well-lg">
	<h2>Users: </h2>
<ul>
  <h5> Sign Up/Login.</h5> Create an account using an active email address.  Login using the email address and password you used during sign up. You can change any of these by clicking on "Edit Profile" under "Accounts" on the navigation bar. 
  <h5> Search/View Material Database.</h5> You can view the Matarial Database which contains the list of materials at Honda and their properties. You can Search, Sort/Filter and then Export the list of materials in the table to an Excel file. You can see a list of test-files available for the materials.
<h5> Groups.</h5> You can see a list of Groups that you are a member of by going to your Homepage. Click on "Visit Group Page" to look at the material associated with the group, in addition to that you can do all the same things that you can do at the "Material List Page". 
<h5> Testfiles. </h5> Users that do not belong to a group can only see if the material files exist or not. Users that do belong to groups can View and Download any testfiles that are displayed on the Group Page.
</p>
<p></p>
   </div></div>
   <div class="col-lg-3"><div class="well well-lg">

<h2>Group Admins: </h2>
<ul>
<h5> Login.</h5>  Login for group admins is similar to users'.
<h5> Search/View Material Databse.</h5>  Same access and features as users.
<h5> Groups.</h5>  In addition to what users can do, group admins/owners can add/delete users from groups and Edit group details. 
<h5> Testfiles </h5> Group admin also get to edit, add, delete testfiles associated with their group.
</ul>
</div></div>
   <div class="col-lg-3"><div class="well well-lg">
<h2>Admin</h2>
<ul>
  <h5> Login.</h5>  An Admin would log in the same way a user would.
  <h5> Search/View Database.</h5>  An admin can edit,add and delete matereials in the list.
 <h5> Groups.</h5>  Admins can edit, add, and delete groups. 
 <h5> Testfiles</h5> Admins can edit, add, and delete testfiles associated with all the groups. 
 
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
